<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">according to the new updated kunark book i just got.. here are the pet commands...:<br>
/pet as you were = returns pet to neutral<br>
/pet attack = tells pet to attack the targeted entity<br>
/pet back off = tells pet to stop attacking<br>
/pet follow me tells pet to follow you<br>
/pet get lost = destroys pet<br>
/pet guard here = makes pet stop in place and guard<br>
/pet guard me = pet will attack anything that attacks you, or that you attack<br>
/pet report health = pet will tell you it's remaining hp<br>
/pet sit down = pet will fall to the ground and rest<br>
/pet stand up = pet will stand back up<br>
/pet target = targets your pet<br>
/pet taunt = tells pet to taunt or stop taunting the enemy<br>
/pet who leader = pet will say who owns it<p>

iv'e found an interesting trick that gets interesting results...<p>

on the second line of your pet hot keys if you made any..<br>
say for instance...pet attack.<br>
in the first line type: /pet attack<br>
in the second line type: /say pet go kill that thing!<p>

when you hit the hotkey, the pet will go after the enemy you targeted, AND everyone will "hear" you tell the pet what to do!  this is an amazing thing that i never knew could be so fun to play with<hr>As all things live.. So too do all things die...Except for me<br>
Wyrmer<br>
13th season iksar necro</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
